^-What You Must Know About Jacoby 2NT

|fp|2|at|A Marty Bergen Audio Visual Lesson  
^-|fp||cs||cp||ht|h|AT|^k@2    By Marty Bergen BBO nickname mbsez; |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.martybergen.com^*N|CP||ht|i|AT|^b@2
Every two months Marty Bergen and Howard produce an animated voice lesson. Using any computer with a browser (PC, Mac, iPad, etc.) you can hear Marty speak for several hours and thoroughly cover his topic. Not only does he discuss the basics, but he includes many "secrets of the experts" as well. I have found these movies very useful and enjoyable. If you are interested in finding out more about these lessons, go to their web site |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/audiolessons/mbaudiolessons.php^*N|CP||AT|. Note that the web site includes some free examples with some interesting bridge puzzles that Marty has created.

I have permission from Marty and Howard to use one example from each lesson to produce a bridge movie. This sampler will give you the flavor of the material that Marty presents and demonstrate his excellent teaching style.

In this movie I chose an example hand from the lesson entitled What You Must Know About Jacoby 2NT. In the lesson Marty gives a detailed explanation of the Jacoby 2NT convention. He explains when it should be used, what opener's rebids are, and the follow ups after opener's rebid. He includes important points regarding hand evaluation and slam bidding. He also discusses splinter bids and when they should and should not be used.

The example I have chosen is Hand 3 from the lesson. It provides two alternative auctions that an expert pair might use. The auctions start with a Jacoby 2N bid and allow the pair to reach an excellent 6S contract despite having only 25 HCP between the two hands. Marty uses the hand to illustrate many important bidding and hand evaluation principles.|ht|y|at|^B@2
Please click the forward arrow to begin the sampler.
^VMarch, 2014|
